/**
 * ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
 * ║  [Admin System] DINOCO LINE Push Governance                      ║
 * ║  Version: V.1.0 (2026-05-07) — R4 social-media-strategist       ║
 * ║    HIGH-1 (frequency cap) + HIGH-2 (quiet hours) + HIGH-3        ║
 * ║    (PDPA §19 granular opt-out) infrastructure foundation.        ║
 * ║  DB_ID: pending sync (set after first WP Code Snippets sync)     ║
 * ║  Description: Centralized LINE push gating layer. Wraps every    ║
 * ║    user-bound LINE message dispatch with frequency cap, quiet   ║
 * ║    hours guard, and per-category opt-in/opt-out compliance.     ║
 * ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
 *
 * PROBLEM (R4 audit findings)
 * ---------------------------
 * HIGH-1  Frequency cap absent — F#1 (Expiry 30/7/1) + F#4 (Anniversary)
 *         + F#10 (Review) + warranty + claim + transfer = 4+ pushes/day
 *         on the same user is reachable. LINE block rate hits 15-25%.
 *
 * HIGH-2  Quiet hours not configured — workers can fire at 03:00 local
 *         time (cron drift / boss manual triggers). Annoyance = block
 *         + Telegram complaints.
 *
 * HIGH-3  PDPA §19 granular consent — current implementation maps
 *         LINE-login => blanket consent. Boss faces ฿1M fine exposure
 *         for marketing pushes (promo / cross-sell) without explicit
 *         double opt-in.
 *
 * SOLUTION
 * --------
 * Single canonical helper layer + admin viewer + member opt-out UI.
 *
 *   - dinoco_line_can_push( $uid, $category, $template_code = '' )
 *       returns array( allowed:bool, reason:string, retry_after_sec:int )
 *
 *   - dinoco_line_log_push( $uid, $category, $template_code, $success )
 *       INSERT into wp_dinoco_line_push_log (audit + cap counter source)
 *
 *   - dinoco_line_get_user_prefs( $uid )      → array of 5 category flags
 *   - dinoco_line_set_user_prefs( $uid, $p )  → write usermeta + audit
 *   - dinoco_line_in_quiet_hours( $uid, $cat ) → bool (transactional bypass)
 *
 * Categories
 *   transactional  — claim status / transfer notify / payment confirm
 *                    ALWAYS allowed, bypasses cap + quiet hours (PDPA §24
 *                    exception for "performance of contract")
 *   expiry         — F#1 30/7/1 day reminders
 *   anniversary    — F#4 1y/2y/3y+ thanks
 *   review         — F#10 30d post-activate review request
 *   marketing      — F#8 extension upsell / promo / cross-sell
 *                    DOUBLE opt-in REQUIRED (PDPA §24) default OFF
 *
 * Caps (admin-tunable wp_option)
 *   Hard cap          — 1 push/user/day  (any non-transactional category)
 *   Soft cap          — 3 push/user/week
 *   Category cap      — 1 expiry/day + 1 lifecycle/day + 1 marketing/day
 *
 * Priority queue (used by Notifier when multiple workers fire same hour)
 *   transactional > expiry > anniversary > review > marketing
 *
 * Quiet hours
 *   Default 09:00–20:00 Asia/Bangkok for non-transactional
 *   Per-user override via wp_usermeta dinoco_sn_quiet_hours_start/end
 *
 * DESIGN PRINCIPLES
 *   - ADDITIVE       — zero behavior change at sites that don't call helpers
 *                      (consumer-side opt-in only)
 *   - DEFENSIVE      — all helpers function_exists wrapped at call sites
 *                      (Notifier integration falls through to legacy path
 *                      when this snippet not yet synced)
 *   - NON-THROWING   — try/catch around every helper; failure = "allow"
 *                      (we never block transactional with an internal bug)
 *   - PDPA AWARE     — marketing default OFF; opt-in audit logged
 *   - LIGHTWEIGHT    — single SELECT COUNT for cap check; no JOINs
 *
 * Admin shortcode: [dinoco_line_push_governance]
 *   3 tabs — Stats / User Audit / Settings
 *
 * Public REST: none (admin viewer only). Saves go through admin-ajax in
 * Header & Forms member dashboard, NOT through this snippet, so we keep
 * the surface minimal.
 *
 * Backward compat: caller code WITHOUT wrapping in `function_exists`
 * (e.g. legacy B2B/B2F push paths) is unchanged. Only Notifier V.0.3 and
 * future SN system push sites consume the gate.
 */

